---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';

const clientNeeds = [
  'Your company\'s exact legal name and the U.S. state it\'s incorporated in.',
  'Your website\'s live domain (e.g. wellpeps.com).',
  'The names of the medical entities that provide care through WellPeps (the same names used on the Notice of Privacy Practices).',
  'Which U.S. states you are actually licensed to operate in — the site currently claims "all 50 states."',
  'Confirmation that a Telehealth Informed Consent appears in the signup flow before a consultation.',
  'For each plan: the real recurring price and how often it charges, any minimum commitment, what happens at renewal, exactly how a customer cancels, your refund policy, and any early-termination fee.',
  'Who owns the WellPeps name, logo, and website content (for the trademark / intellectual-property lines), and whether any trademarks are registered.',
  'Whether you send marketing text messages — a simple yes or no.',
  'How, and how far in advance, you\'ll notify people when these terms change.',
  'The date this goes live.',
];
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="The terms that govern your use of the WellPeps website and platform."
  clientNeeds={clientNeeds}
>
  <p class="legal__meta">
    Effective Date: <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: the date this goes live</span><br />
    Last Updated: <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: same as the date above for the first version</span>
  </p>

  <h2>1. Acceptance of These Terms</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms of Use (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) are a binding agreement between you and
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: your exact legal name, e.g. WellPeps, Inc., a Delaware corporation</span>,
    together with its affiliates (&ldquo;WellPeps,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or
    &ldquo;our&rdquo;), governing your access to and use of the website located at
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: your live domain</span>, our patient portal, and related services
    (collectively, the &ldquo;Platform&rdquo;). By accessing or using the Platform, you agree to
    these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Platform.
  </p>

  <h2>2. What WellPeps Is — and Is Not</h2>
  <p>
    WellPeps is a technology platform that connects individuals with independent, licensed
    healthcare providers and licensed pharmacy partners. WellPeps itself does not practice medicine
    or pharmacy and does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. All medical services
    available through the Platform are provided by
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: the names of the affiliated medical group(s) — must match the names used on the Notice of Privacy Practices</span>,
    independent practices whose providers exercise independent clinical judgment. All prescriptions
    are filled by independent licensed pharmacies, including compounding pharmacies.
  </p>
  <div class="callout callout--note">
    <strong>Depends on your lawyer's corporate-structure decision</strong>
    <p>
      The description above assumes a standard telehealth company structure.
      <span class="ph ph--legal">Lawyer: confirm the actual corporate structure before launch — it changes this section, the Notice of Privacy Practices framing, and the medical-disclaimer wording across the whole site.</span>
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>3. Not for Medical Emergencies</h2>
  <p>
    The Platform is not intended for medical emergencies. If you are experiencing a medical
    emergency, call 911 or go to the nearest emergency room immediately. If you are experiencing a
    mental health crisis, call or text 988 (Suicide &amp; Crisis Lifeline).
  </p>

  <h2>4. Eligibility</h2>
  <p>
    You must be at least 18 years old, reside in a U.S. state where the services you request are
    available, and be able to form a binding contract to use the Platform. The services are
    available in <span class="ph ph--you">You confirm: the states you are actually licensed in. The site currently claims &ldquo;all 50 states&rdquo; — that needs to be verified against your licensing before launch.</span>.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Telehealth Services and Informed Consent</h2>
  <p>
    Before receiving any telehealth consultation, you will be asked to review and accept a separate
    Telehealth Informed Consent describing the nature, benefits, and limitations of telehealth care.
    <span class="ph ph--you">You confirm: a standalone Telehealth Informed Consent exists in the signup flow. Several states require specific consent language.</span>
    A consultation does not guarantee that a provider will issue a prescription; treatment decisions
    are made solely by the provider based on their clinical judgment.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Prescription Products, Including Compounded Medications</h2>
  <p>
    Some products available through the Platform are compounded medications prepared by licensed
    compounding pharmacies. Compounded medications are not FDA-approved. The FDA does not review
    compounded drugs for safety, effectiveness, or quality before they are dispensed. Registration
    of a compounding facility with the FDA is not a determination by the FDA that any drug produced
    there is safe or effective.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Accounts and Security</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all
    activity under your account. You agree to provide accurate, current information — including your
    legal name, date of birth, and shipping address — and to update it promptly. Notify us
    immediately at <a href="mailto:hello@wellpeps.com">hello@wellpeps.com</a> of any unauthorized
    use.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Plans, Pricing, Billing, Renewal, and Cancellation</h2>
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>The highest-risk section — the terms here must match what you actually charge</strong>
    <p>
      Federal rules and about 25 state auto-renewal laws require the real billing terms to be shown
      here and at checkout, just as prominently as the advertised price. Getting this wrong is a
      common source of legal trouble, so the details below have to be exact.
      <span class="ph ph--you">You provide, for each plan: the true recurring charge and how often it bills; any minimum commitment and total price; what happens at renewal and the renewal price; exactly how and by when a customer cancels; your refund policy; and any early-termination fee.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
  <p>
    Plan pricing, billing frequency, commitment terms, renewal terms, and cancellation instructions
    are stated at checkout and summarized here:
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: the finalized plan table (your lawyer approves the wording once you supply the numbers)</span>.
    You may cancel by
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: how a customer cancels. Note: California and several other states require an online cancellation option if signup was online.</span>.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Acceptable Use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide false or misleading health or identity information to obtain services or prescriptions;</li>
    <li>Use the Platform on behalf of another person or share, resell, or transfer any medication received;</li>
    <li>Access or attempt to access another user&rsquo;s account or any non-public area of the Platform;</li>
    <li>Scrape, reverse-engineer, or interfere with the Platform, or introduce malicious code;</li>
    <li>Use the Platform in violation of any applicable law.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms, subject to appropriate
    continuity-of-care handling by the treating provider.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    The Platform and its content (excluding your personal information) are owned by
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: the company that owns the website and content</span> or its licensors and are protected by
    intellectual-property laws. We grant you a limited, revocable, non-exclusive, non-transferable
    license to use the Platform for personal, non-commercial purposes. &ldquo;WellPeps&rdquo; and
    associated logos are trademarks of
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: the trademark owner, and whether any registrations are filed</span>.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Communications and Text Messages</h2>
  <p>
    By providing your phone number, you consent to receive service-related calls and text messages
    from us and our providers and pharmacy partners.
    <span class="ph ph--you">You confirm: whether you send marketing texts. If yes, a separate text-marketing opt-in with STOP/HELP wording, message frequency, and rate disclosures is legally required — tell us and the web team will add it.</span>
    Message and data rates may apply. Reply STOP to opt out of texts.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Your use of the Platform is also governed by our
    <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> and, with respect to protected health information,
    the <a href="/notice-of-privacy-practices">Notice of Privacy Practices</a>. For California
    residents, our <a href="/your-privacy-choices">Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information</a>
    page describes your opt-out rights.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Disclaimers</h2>
  <p>
    EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY STATED, THE PLATFORM IS PROVIDED &ldquo;AS IS&rdquo; AND &ldquo;AS
    AVAILABLE&rdquo; WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF
    MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. WELLPEPS DOES NOT
    WARRANT ANY PARTICULAR HEALTH OUTCOME. THIS SECTION DOES NOT LIMIT ANY WARRANTY OR RIGHT THAT
    CANNOT BE DISCLAIMED UNDER APPLICABLE LAW.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, WELLPEPS AND ITS OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, AND
    AGENTS WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES,
    AND OUR AGGREGATE LIABILITY ARISING OUT OF THE PLATFORM WILL NOT EXCEED
    <span class="ph ph--legal">Lawyer: set the liability cap — commonly the amounts paid in the prior 12 months, or $100, whichever is greater.</span>.
    THIS LIMITATION DOES NOT APPLY TO LIABILITY THAT CANNOT BE LIMITED BY LAW, AND NOTHING IN THESE
    TERMS LIMITS THE PROFESSIONAL RESPONSIBILITY OF TREATING PROVIDERS.
  </p>

  <h2>15. Indemnification</h2>
  <p>
    You agree to indemnify and hold harmless WellPeps from claims arising out of your violation of
    these Terms, your misuse of the Platform, or your provision of false information, except to the
    extent caused by our own negligence or misconduct.
  </p>

  <h2>16. Dispute Resolution</h2>
  <div class="callout callout--note">
    <strong>A business-and-legal decision — not a default</strong>
    <p>
      <span class="ph ph--legal">Lawyer + client: choose how disputes are handled — (a) courts only, (b) arbitration with a class waiver and a 30-day opt-out, or (c) a small-claims carve-out variant — and pick the arbitration forum and who pays the fees. Arbitration clauses in healthcare-adjacent contracts draw regulator scrutiny.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
  <p>
    <span class="ph ph--legal">Lawyer: insert the chosen dispute-resolution clause. If arbitration is chosen it must include an informal-resolution first step with a notice address, a small-claims carve-out, consumer fee allocation, a 30-day opt-out mechanism, and severability of the class waiver.</span>
  </p>

  <h2>17. Governing Law</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of
    <span class="ph ph--legal">Lawyer: the governing-law state — usually the company's home state.</span>,
    without regard to conflict-of-law rules.
  </p>

  <h2>18. Changes to These Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be notified by
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: how you'll notify people — email, an in-account banner, or both</span> at least
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: how much advance notice, e.g. 30 days</span> before taking effect. Continued
    use after the effective date constitutes acceptance. Changes to auto-renewal or pricing terms
    will be disclosed in the manner required by applicable state law.
  </p>

  <h2>19. Termination</h2>
  <p>
    You may stop using the Platform and close your account at any time by contacting
    <a href="mailto:hello@wellpeps.com">hello@wellpeps.com</a>. Termination does not by itself
    cancel an active paid plan — see Section 8 for cancellation. Sections that by their nature
    survive termination (including Sections 10 and 13–17) survive.
  </p>

  <h2>20. Miscellaneous</h2>
  <p>
    If any provision of these Terms is held unenforceable, the remainder remains in effect. These
    Terms, together with the Privacy Policy, Notice of Privacy Practices, Telehealth Informed
    Consent, and any plan-specific terms presented at checkout, are the entire agreement between you
    and WellPeps regarding the Platform. You may not assign these Terms; we may assign them in
    connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets with notice to you.
  </p>

  <h2>21. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: your company's legal name</span><br />
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: your registered business address</span><br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:hello@wellpeps.com">hello@wellpeps.com</a> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Phone:
    <a href="tel:+18339357377">(833) 935-7377</a> (Mon–Fri, 9am–6pm ET)
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
